SIMPLE: acronychal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acronychal
<hw>A*cron"ych*al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'akro`nychos</grk>
at nightfall; <grk>'a`kros</grk> + <grk>ny`x</grk> night.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>Rising at sunset and setting at sunrise, as a
star; -- opposed to <ant>cosmical</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The word is sometimes incorrectly written
<xex>acronical</xex>, <xex>achronychal</xex>, <xex>acronichal</xex>, and
<xex>acronical</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acronycally</ent>⟦br⟧
